Business Brief -- Goodyear Tire  Rubber Co.:
   Firm Approves Initial Phase
   Of Resin Plant's Expansion
The Akron, Ohio, company said it did not immediately know
if the expansion would create new jobs. The Point Pleasant
facility currently employs about 580 workers.
   Goodyear said it is currently engaged in talks to sell its
polyester business, which would include the expanded plant.
The expansion is scheduled for completion by the first
quarter of 1994, the company said.